article.headline: Rutgers coach stays at 700 wins
article.linkText: Pulling rank: Temple scores upset over Rutgers
article.story:
PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Cynthia Jordan scored 20 of her 28 points in
the first half to lead Temple to a 71-60 upset over No. 22 Rutgers
on Monday.

Temple (5-3) led by nine at halftime before Rutgers (5-2) cut
the Owls' lead to five with 18:32 remaining. But a 13-2 Temple run
over the next 3:07 pushed its lead to 44-28, and the Owls led by as
many as 20 points.

Candice Dupree added 16 points for Temple and Kamesha Hairston
added 13.

Matee Ajavon led Rutgers with 18 points. The Scarlet Knights
struggled from the field (24-of-62) and shot just 39 percent. The
Owls shot 18-of-34 (53 percent) from the field.

The victory was Temple's first over a ranked opponent since an
81-68 win over No. 20 Rutgers on March 10, 1989. The Owls had
previously lost this season to No. 2 LSU and No. 1 Tennessee.
